\subsection{Statistical Corroboration via ANOVA F-Test}
\label{sec:expanded_anova}
% ----------------------------------------------------------

Following the two-level validation strategy introduced in
Section~\ref{sec:anova-bridge}, an ANOVA F-test pipeline was applied to the expanded
cohort using the same implementation described in Section~\ref{sec:anova-bridge}.
For each subtype under OvR binarisation, features were ranked by their F-statistic
and the top-$k$ features were used to train a Random Forest classifier. F1-score was
computed as a function of $k$ (from $k = 5$ to $k = 100$) using 5-fold
stratified cross-validation, with the same class-weighting and stratification
strategy as in the pilot study. Both feature configurations (miRNA only; miRNA +
clinical) were evaluated in parallel.

\subsubsection{Performance Curves and Optimal Feature Counts}

Table~\ref{tab:anova_expanded_summary} summarises the key results from the ANOVA
sweep. A comparison with the pilot-study values (Table~\ref{tab:anova_summary}) is
possible at the level of best F1-score and initial F1-score (at $k = 5$),
though the optimal $k$ values are not directly comparable due to the different
feature-space sizes.

