\subsubsection{Doubly-Validated miRNA Panels}

As in the pilot study, the primary purpose of the ANOVA sweep is not to produce
a standalone classifier, but to cross-reference its top-ranked features with those
identified by the XGBoost booster, producing \textbf{doubly-validated candidate
miRNA panels} that are supported by two independent methods: one multivariate and
model-embedded, one marginal and model-agnostic. Features that survive both filters
independently are the strongest biomarker candidates, because their discriminative
power cannot be attributed to model-specific artefacts or to correlation with
confounders.

